snippet.textDisplay: Maybe the main reason it's spreading in the U.S. is because our experts keep telling us to not wear masks in public! Think that might have something to do with it? "But we'd deplete the supplies of healthcare!" Then don't wear masks that healthcare uses. Make your own. Use a dust mask, a pollen mask, a homemade mask, a bandana. Anything to hinder the expulsion of droplets whenever you talk, sneeze, or cough. Again, it isn't rocket science. But our experts seem to be moving us toward economic ruin in their approach. Those Asian countries above aren't shutting their economies down, and yet their case load remains relatively low even though they are among the most densely populated places on earth. Look at any photo of people on the streets there, what do you see? Universal mask wearing, that's what. Go into any crowded grocery store or Walmart here. What do you see? Only a smattering of brave souls wearing masks. Why? Because most people are trusting their medical experts and authorities and dutifully refraining from wearing masks. Wake up people. The experts aren't always right.

snippet.textDisplay: Just wanted to tell my story on my experience with covid-19, it is currently day 4 going onto day 5 since first showing symptoms since me and my girlfriend have gotten ill and it's so easy to identify this because of how brutal it is. My girlfriend is 18 and healthy and earlier today I've been terrified by her reactions to the illness as she was basically suffocating, with her chest feeling heavy and sore with a congested nose stopping her from breathing through her nose, making it even more difficult to deal with. Then there are the aches that travel through your body, the fatigue, the chills, the headaches, diarrhoea, the fever and this is hard on 2 people that aren't classed as vulnerable in any way. Take this virus seriously because from my experience and witnessing my girlfriends too, I believe that anybody with underlying problems like COPD would be at HUGE risk. Please stay home unless absolutely necessary and do your part to protect the old and vulnerable.
